<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-21T20:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-21T20:36:00-05:00" n="1077" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1077">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/1346</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from">Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-21T19:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1916, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>301. Department’s 307, August 19, noon. Cabrera to-day promised
                            instruction to State Governments to desist from action seeking to compel
                            operation mines before protection and transportation can be guaranteed.
                            As to matter extension time payment taxes last tercio without penalty
                            promised consideration question.</p>
                        <p>As to general question mining taxes status about same as stated in my
                            229, July 21, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>